  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For campaign to prevent the southward expansion of Chile&apos;s farmed salmon industry, which has thus far brought destructive social and environmental impacts to the Los Lagos region. Currently, the industry is working to expand into southern regions of Aysen and Magellan region. Funds will used for public communications and meetings with representatives of government, artisanal fisherman, tour operators, scientists, and the general public. Ecoceanos specifically aims to increase public oversight related to pending salmon farm concessions; the use of public funds in these developments; salmon farm waste management; and the volume of antibiotics and other harmful chemicals used by salmon companies in Chile on annual basis</narrative>
  </description>
